BIOGRAPHY

Entered the MSU program in 2022

M.Ed. in Community Development and Action, Vanderbilt University, 2020

B.S. in Psychology & Educational Studies, Manchester University, 2018

RESEARCH

My research interests fall within two broad categories. The first is positive youth development in school and community settings. The second is community-engaged learning in higher education settings. I strive to conduct community-engaged and -based research (i.e., action research, community-based participatory research) that promotes social justice and equity.
